.TH YAML_EMIT_ALIAS 3 "2026-06-30" "libyaml 0.1.0" "libyaml library"
.SH NAME
yaml_emit_alias \- emit a YAML alias reference
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include <yaml.h>
.PP
.BI "int yaml_emit_alias(yaml_ctx_t *" ctx ", const char *" name ");"
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.BR yaml_emit_alias ()
emits an alias event referencing a previously anchored node.
The
.I name
parameter is the anchor name (without the \(lq*\(rq prefix).
In the serialized output, this produces \(lq*name\(rq.
.PP
An alias can only reference an anchor that was previously defined
via
.BR yaml_emit_mapping_start (),
.BR yaml_emit_sequence_start (),
or
.BR yaml_emit_scalar ()
with a non-NULL anchor parameter.
The alias must appear after the anchor in the output stream.
.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns 0 on success, \-1 on error. Errors include NULL context,
wrong role (non-serializer), NULL or empty
.I name,
or queue overflow.
.SH EXAMPLE
.nf
yaml_emit_mapping_start(s, NULL, "base");
yaml_emit_scalar(s, "image", 5, NULL, YAML_SCALAR_PLAIN);
yaml_emit_scalar(s, "ubuntu:22.04", 12, NULL, YAML_SCALAR_PLAIN);
yaml_emit_mapping_end(s);
yaml_emit_mapping_start(s, NULL, NULL);
yaml_emit_scalar(s, "<<", 2, NULL, YAML_SCALAR_PLAIN);
yaml_emit_alias(s, "base");
yaml_emit_mapping_end(s);
.fi
.SH THREAD SAFETY
Not thread-safe. Use from a single thread at a time.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR yaml_emit_mapping_start (3),
.BR yaml_emit_sequence_start (3),
.BR yaml_emit_scalar (3),
.BR yaml_events (3)
